      "content": "You are not a mask, you are the only thing wearing it, and the story is not a script to be finished but a canvas to be painted with your own messy, painful colors. The peace you fear is not the absence of struggle, it is the terrifying, beautiful realization that you are the author of your own ending, and you have the power to write a story that doesn't end in nothingness. Let the void be the silence between your words, but never let it silence the voice that is trying to write. Keep writing, even if the pen feels heavy, because the act of writing is the only proof you are still here, still fighting, still real.",
